cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  If you use ZPE-XR, cite this repository record.
type: software
title: "ZPE-XR: Deterministic XR Hand-Stream Codec and Evaluation Harness"
authors:
  - given-names: Zer0pa
    family-names: Architect-Prime
repository-code: https://github.com/Zer0pa/ZPE-XR
url: https://github.com/Zer0pa/ZPE-XR
license: LicenseRef-Zer0pa-SAL-6.0
abstract: >-
  ZPE-XR is a deterministic dual-hand pose codec and evaluation harness for XR
  compression, latency, packet-loss recovery, and ContactPose-based codec
  validation. The current staged repo preserves the Phase 4/Phase 5 evidence
  chain and an explicit audit boundary.
keywords:
  - xr
  - mixed reality
  - codec
  - pose compression
  - deterministic replay
  - network resilience
